quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  101,10,"And what can make you know what that is?"
  101,11,"It is a Fire, intensely hot."
  102,7,"Then you will surely see it with the eye of certainty.{1}",footnotes:1:[i.e., with actual eyesight.]
  102,8,"Then you will surely be asked that Day about pleasure.{1}",footnotes:1:[i.e., the comforts of worldly life and whether you were grateful to Allāh for His blessings.]
  104,1,"Woe to every scorner and mocker"
  104,2,"Who collects wealth and [continuously] counts it.{1}",footnotes:1:[Rather than spending in the way of Allāh.]
  104,3,"He thinks that his wealth will make him immortal."